definition: to overflow/(literary) excessive/old variant of 鎰|镒[yi4]

to go out/to come out/to occur/to produce/to go beyond/to rise/to put forth/to happen/(used after a verb to indicate an outward direction or a positive result)/classifier for dramas, plays, operas etc
variant of 出[chu1] (classifier for plays or chapters of classical novels)

sentences.english: She poured too vigorously and half the gingerale foamed away.
sentences.chinese: 她倒得太猛，一半的姜汽水冒泡溢出。

sentences.english: Cannot change text flow because columns will overflow into margins .
sentences.chinese: 不能改变文字排列，因为栏将溢出到页边距中。

sentences.english: Heat oil. Add Chng Kee's Sambal Belacan Chilli Paste and stir-fry until fragrant.
sentences.chinese: 用热油翻炒庄记参芭芭拉煎辣椒酱至香味溢出。

sentences.english: Buffer overflows are the cause of many a security bug.
sentences.chinese: 缓冲区溢出是许多安全性问题的起因。

sentences.english: An oil spill in Australia blackens white sand beaches.
sentences.chinese: 澳大利亚石油溢出污染着白色海滩。

sentences.english: It is a cornucopia of riches, symbolized by the overflowing market basket.
sentences.chinese: 这是一个财富的丰饶角，被满溢出的果菜篮体现。

sentences.english: One reason for such results is that inter-industry spillovers are neglected.
sentences.chinese: 对此，以往的研究常常忽略行业间溢出。

sentences.english: Constant bubbling sends waves of lava lapping over the rim.
sentences.chinese: 不断的鼓泡会将起伏的熔岩从边缘溢出。

sentences.english: The content frame should not include overset text.
sentences.chinese: 这个内容框架不能包含溢出文字。

sentences.english: The champagne is spilling out of the bottle.
sentences.chinese: 香槟从瓶子中不断地溢出来。

sentences.english: However, none of this lets developers ignore buffer overflows.
sentences.chinese: 然而，没有哪种方法允许开发人员忽略缓冲区溢出。

sentences.english: Take the pan away quickly; it's boiling over.
sentences.chinese: 快把锅子端开，里面的东西都煮得溢出来了。

sentences.english: Rinse off any emerging brake fluid thoroughly with water.
sentences.chinese: 用水彻底将溢出的制动液冲洗掉。

sentences.english: Turns overflow-error checking for integer operations on or off.
sentences.chinese: 打开或关闭整数操作的溢出错误检查。

sentences.english: She sopped up the spilt milk with a cloth.
sentences.chinese: 她用一块布抹去溢出的牛奶。

sentences.english: You have to keep watching to prevent the milk from boiling over .
sentences.chinese: 你要看住，不要让牛奶溢出来。

definition: to gush/to gush out/to pour out
to be full to overflowing/to be brimming over with
to leak out/to release (liquid or gas)
to overflow/(literary) excessive/old variant of 鎰|镒[yi4]
spout/spray/belch/to well up/to puff out/to spurt out
to let drip/to trickle down/to shed (tears)
(of a perfume or a foul odor) permeating the whole place/(of grease etc) dripping everywhere/flowing all over the place
